<paragraph base="F55667084" id="IFRS17_B7"><paranum>B7</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 17"/><data name="paranum" value="B7"/></prolog><body><p id="IFRS17_P0584">The definition of an <xref base="F55666957" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0532">insurance contract<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0186"/></ph></xref> requires that one party accepts significant <xref base="F55666976" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0539">insurance risk<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0190"/></ph></xref> from another party. <xref base="F59236092" href="IFRS17_TOC.dita#IFRS17_TOC0001" id="IFRS17_X0545">IFRS 17</xref> defines insurance risk as &#x2018;risk, other than <xref base="F55666934" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0524">financial risk<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0129"/></ph></xref>, transferred from the holder of a contract to the issuer&#x2019;. A contract that exposes the issuer to financial risk without significant insurance risk is not an insurance contract.</p></body></paragraph>